# DO NOT enable `ignore-scripts=true` here.
#
# Why we'd want to: it blocks dependencies' lifecycle scripts (preinstall,
# install, postinstall), which is a common supply-chain hardening measure —
# a malicious package can't run arbitrary code on `npm install`.
#
# Why we can't: vue-demi relies on its own postinstall hook to swap
# `lib/index.cjs` to a Vue-version-specific build. Without it, the default
# entry exports the Vue 2 (pre-2.7) shape, which is missing several APIs
# that downstream packages (pinia, @vueuse/core, vue-frag, vue-codemirror6,
# and more) import. You get build/runtime errors like:
#
#   export 'hasInjectionContext' (imported as 'hasInjectionContext') was not found in 'vue-demi'
#   export 'Fragment' (imported as 'Fragment') was not found in 'vue-demi'
#
# You can try enabling this flag, but you'd then have to write a script
# that performs the fix yourself.

# ignore-scripts=true
